What is Project Loom ?

Project Loom is an OpenJDK project that introduced virtual threads (finalized in Java 21)
and continues to be enhanced in Java 25.


🔷 Simple way to remember
Project Loom = umbrella project
Virtual Threads = main feature
Java 25 = improved version, not the origin

🔷 Quick analogy
Think of it like:
Project Loom = Electric car technology
Virtual Threads = Battery system
Java 21 = First working car
Java 25 = Better, faster upgraded model

